      "message": "\u003e I would just leave `deperecated`. Peeople might continue contributing to it. It won\u0027t happen but they technically could.\n\nWell, if you just see `deprecated` without pointers to the *non-deprecated* version then people may just thing that this isn\u0027t maintained anymore, which isn\u0027t true.\n\nThe plugin continues its development on GerritHub and is published on GitHub; after 5 years all the code becomes Apache 2.0 and can be re-contributed to the stable branches of this plugin.\n\nSo, technically, only the `master` branch is deprecated, the stable branches aren\u0027t.",
